# Phone Inbox Workflow

The project phone inbox lives at **`markdowns/PHONE-INBOX.md`**.

## Required behavior

1. At the beginning of each new user session/message, read `markdowns/PHONE-INBOX.md`.
2. Treat unchecked entries (`- [ ]`) in the `New` section as pending tasks or requests from the user.
3. When an inbox item is completed during this session, mark it completed by either:
   - changing `- [ ]` to `- [x]` and wrapping text in strikethrough (`~~...~~`), or
   - moving it under `Completed`.
4. Never delete items silently unless the user explicitly asks to purge/archive old completed entries.

## User intents to support

When the user asks:
- "check phone inbox"
- "scan inbox"
- "what came from phone"
- "process phone tasks"

Read `markdowns/PHONE-INBOX.md` and respond based on current unchecked items.

